# Polite Craft — extension development

## Source of truth

- Edit only `src/`. Run `npm run build` to refresh `dist/`.
- Do not hand-edit `dist/`.

## Manifest V3

- `background.js` is a service worker: no `document`, no DOM APIs.
- Use `chrome.runtime.onMessage` / `sendMessage` for content ↔ background communication.
- Persist settings with `chrome.storage.local`.

## GitHub content script

- `content.js` injects a toolbar below comment composers on `https://github.com/*`.
- GitHub is a React SPA: keep `MutationObserver` and multiple insert paths (footer, wrapper, sibling, fallback).
- Test DOM changes with `npm test` and manual verification on a real GitHub PR/Issue page.

## API & secrets

- DeepSeek API key comes from user settings only — never commit keys or `.env`.
- Host permission for `api.deepseek.com` is required for fetch from the service worker.

## Testing

After changing `background.js` or `content.js`:

```bash
npm test
npm run build
```

## Style

- Match existing code: plain JS, minimal abstractions, focused diffs.
- User-facing strings in the extension UI are Chinese; code comments may be Chinese or English.
